    "Nonetheless, the medical domain introduces elevated concerns regarding safety and privacy, necessitating detailed analysis regarding the performance and limitations of LLMs to address the inherent risks such as hallucination, bias, and reasoning deficiencies 6.",
    "Since its inception by Medicare in 1983, DRG has served as the foundation for the inpatient prospective payment system within the United States 7.",
    "Each distinct DRG code is delineated by a particular set of patient attributes, including principal diagnosis, specific secondary diagnoses, procedures, sex and discharge status 8.",
    "Traditionally, the assignment of DRGs constitutes a labor-intensive manual endeavor undertaken by coding specialists, typically subsequent to a patient's discharge.",
    "Given the pivotal role of DRGs and their bundled metrics (e.g., case-mix index, geometric length of stay) in the operational and financial performance of hospitals, a pressing interest exists in the accurate early prediction of DRGs during a patient's hospitalization."
